    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that but my doctor is always so rushed and barely listens to me. i've been doing lots of cardio and eating really well so my circulation feels great. if i'm feeling this healthy, isn't the risk of a clot actually lower? like, wouldn't a lower dose like 2mg be more \"natural\" for my body right now since i'm not struggling? i just want some reassurance that a slight reduction won't blow up in my face.",
